@page "/templates"
@layout PublicLayout

<PageTitle>Report Examples - grow.IT</PageTitle>

<div class="contact-page footer-info-page">
    <section class="contact-hero">
        <span class="contact-kicker">Reports</span>
        <h1>Reports should come from saved data, not late-night copy and paste.</h1>
        <p>Grow.IT helps founders turn service records, outcomes, programs, funds, and ASC progress into usable reports and portfolio content.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="contact-grid-section">
        <div class="contact-grid">
            <article class="contact-card">
                <h2>Impact Summary</h2>
                <p>Show who was served, what changed, and which outcomes were documented over a selected period.</p>
            </article>
            <article class="contact-card">
                <h2>Service Cost Detail</h2>
                <p>Break down services provided, program connection, funding source, and the dollar value of support delivered.</p>
            </article>
            <article class="contact-card">
                <h2>Funding Readiness</h2>
                <p>Use organization profile, documents, follow-ups, reports, and ASC evidence to see what still needs to be strengthened.</p>
            </article>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="contact-form-section">
        <article class="contact-form-card">
            <h2>What makes Grow.IT reports different?</h2>
            <p>The report starts with data the organization already entered. That means less manual rebuilding, cleaner exports, and stronger consistency between board reports, funder reports, donor updates, and internal planning.</p>
        </article>
    </section>

    <section class="contact-cta">
        <div class="contact-cta-card">
            <h2>Want report examples for your demo?</h2>
            <p>We can walk through impact, service cost, donor, program, and readiness reporting using your operating model.</p>
            <div class="contact-cta-actions">
                <a href="/contact?demo=1&subject=Report%20Demo%20Request" class="btn btn-primary">Request Report Demo</a>
                <a href="/docs" class="btn btn-outline">How It Works</a>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</div>
